  "text": "Our results should be interpreted in the context of some limitations. Our measures of depression, anxiety, and family functioning, especially the relation between parents and patients, were rather global and not specific enough to distinguish unshared and shared environmental issues. We constructed a new measure of total FHA, which was related to an EOA. However, our measure of paternal FHA was not, and familial alcoholism in EOA is especially seen in the paternal line [CITATION_1] . Finally, we used the family history approach and collected information on family members from our patients rather than from these family members themselves.",
